 EVALUATION PROCEDURE                                             3925 1451
                                                                  3925 1451
 Adopted procedure is based on careful theoretical                3925 1451
 analysis utilizing available experimental data and               3925 1451
 nuclear reaction model calculations.                             3925 1451
                                                                  3925 1451
 Available experimental data were interpreted  using              3925 1451
 nuclear reaction model code EMPIRE-2.19b27 by                    3925 1451
 M. Herman et al [He01, He02]. This code integrates               3925 1451
 into a single system a number of important modules               3925 1451
 and features:                                                    3925 1451
                                                                  3925 1451
 - Spherical and deformed Optical Model including                 3925 1451
   coupled-channels (ECIS03 by J. Raynal)                         3925 1451
 - Hauser-Feshbach statistical model including                    3925 1451
   HRTW width fluctuation correction                              3925 1451
 - Quantum-mechanical MSD TUL model (codes ORION &                3925 1451
   TRISTAN by H. Lenske), and MSC NVWY model                      3925 1451
 - Exciton model with angular momentum coupling                   3925 1451
   (code DEGAS by E. Betak and P. Oblozinsky) that                3925 1451
   represents a good approximation to the DSD model               3925 1451
 - Exciton model with Iwamoto-Harada cluster                      3925 1451
   emission and Kalbach systematic angular distr.                 3925 1451
   (code PCROSS by R.Capote et al)                                3925 1451
 - Complete gamma-ray cascade after emission of                   3925 1451
   each particle, including realistic treatment of                3925 1451
   discrete transitions                                           3925 1451
 - Access to OM segment of the RIPL-2 library [Ri03]              3925 1451
 - Built-in input parameter files, such as masses,                3925 1451
   level density, discrete levels, fission barriers               3925 1451
   and gamma strength functions  based on the RIPL-2              3925 1451
   library [Ri03]                                                 3925 1451
 - Automatic retrieval of experimental data from the              3925 1451
   EXFOR/CSISRS library                                           3925 1451
 - ENDF-6 formatting (code EMPEND by A. Trkov)                    3925 1451
   coupled to graphical presentation capabilities                 3925 1451
   (code ZVView by V. Zerkin) through the chain of                3925 1451
   PrePro codes by R. Cullen                                      3925 1451
 - Checking codes (CHECKR, FIZCON, PSYCHE)                        3925 1451
